# Tables

Zolt supports powerful grid tables with cell merging, headers, and alignment.

---

## Basic Syntax

Wrap table content between `[[table]]` and `[[/table]]`:

```zolt
[[table]]
| Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Data 1 | Data 2 | Data 3 |
| Data 4 | Data 5 | Data 6 |
[[/table]]
```

### Explanation

- `[[table]]` — Start the table
- `| ... |` — Table rows
- `| :--- |` — Header row separator
- `[[/table]]` — End the table

---

## Header Cells

Mark header cells with `[h]`:

```zolt
[[table]]
| [h] Name | [h] Age | [h] City |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Alice | 30 | New York |
| Bob | 25 | London |
[[/table]]
```

### Result

| [h] Name | [h] Age | [h] City |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Alice | 30 | New York |
| Bob | 25 | London |

---

## Cell Alignment

Control alignment with separator position:

| Syntax | Alignment |
|--------|-----------|
| `:---` | Left |
| `:---:` | Center |
| `---:` | Right |

### Examples

```zolt
[[table]]
| Left | Center | Right |
| :--- | :---: | ---: |
| Data | Data | Data |
[[/table]]
```

---

## Cell Merging

### Horizontal Merge ( colspan)

```zolt
[[table]]
| [h] Header | [h] Header |
| :--- | :--- |
| [colspan=2] Merged Cell | 
| Cell 1 | Cell 2 |
[[/table]]
```

### Vertical Merge (rowspan)

```zolt
[[table]]
| [h] Header | [h] Data |
| :--- | :--- |
| [rowspan=2] Merged | Row 1 |
| | Row 2 |
| Normal | Data |
[[/table]]
```

---

## Complex Example

```zolt
[[table id=sales]]
| [h] Category | [h] Q1 | [h] Q2 | [h] Q3 | [h] Q4 |
| :--- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| [rowspan=2] Electronics | $50K | $60K | $70K | $80K |
| | 45% | 50% | 55% | 60% |
| Clothing | $30K | $35K | $40K | $45K |
| [colspan=2] [h] Total | $80K | $95K | $110K | $125K |
[[/table]]
```

---

## Table Attributes

Add IDs and classes:

```zolt
[[table id=data-table class=striped]]
| Header |
| :--- |
| Data |
[[/table]]
```

---

## Styling Inside Tables

Apply inline styles to table content:

```zolt
[[table]]
| Normal | [h] Header | Important{color=red} |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Data 1 | Data 2 | Data 3{fontWeight=bold} |
[[/table]]
```

---

## Use Cases

### Financial Report

```zolt
[[table id=financials]]
| [h] Item | [h] 2024 | [h] 2025 | [h] Change |
| :--- | ---: | ---: | ---: |
| Revenue | $1,000,000 | $1,250,000 | +25%{color=green} |
| Expenses | $750,000 | $800,000 | +7%{color=orange} |
| [colspan=2] [h] Profit | $250,000 | $450,000 | +80%{color=green fontWeight=bold} |
[[/table]]
```

### Technical Specification

```zolt
[[table id=specs]]
| [h] Component | [h] Specification | [h] Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| [rowspan=2] CPU | 3.2 GHz | 8-core |
| | Apple M2 | ARM-based |
| Memory | 16GB | Unified |
| Storage | 512GB | SSD |
[[/table]]
```

### Comparison Table

```zolt
[[table id=comparison]]
| [h] Feature | [h] Basic | [h] Pro | [h] Enterprise |
| :--- | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| Users | 1 | 10 | Unlimited |
| Storage | 5GB | 100GB | 1TB |
| Support | Email | Priority | Dedicated |
| Price | Free | $29/mo | $99/mo |
[[/table]]
```

---

## Best Practices

1. **Always use headers** `[h]` for the first row
2. **Keep tables readable** with proper alignment
3. **Use IDs** for linking and styling
4. **Merge wisely** don't over-complicate
5. **Test rendering** especially with complex merges

